01:08.960 --> 01:10.920
You really want to know?
I'm mystified.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.920
Seaweed?

01:13.000 --> 01:15.560
- Ah, yes.
- <i>You take the cars</i>

01:15.640 --> 01:18.320
and they are dented,
or lodged in cement, or this one,

01:18.400 --> 01:20.520
with seaweed in the engine.
How does it happen?

01:20.560 --> 01:23.040
Do you know what salt
water does to an engine?

01:23.080 --> 01:25.360
I'm sorry, Dieter. I, um...

01:25.440 --> 01:27.720
I ran out of road, there
was nowhere else to go.

01:27.760 --> 01:30.400
<i>Hey, at least in Toronto
there's only fresh water.</i>

01:30.440 --> 01:33.160
- <i>Please, keep the car out of the lake.</i>
- I have insurance.

01:33.200 --> 01:36.120
Yes, but it's still a car.
It has feelings, Frank.

01:40.120 --> 01:42.120
[ arguing ]

01:42.160 --> 01:44.120
<i>- You fucking whore!</i>
- I'll call you back.

01:48.840 --> 01:50.840
<i>Either you move or
I'm gonna move you.</i>

01:51.120 --> 01:52.480
<i>- Move out of the way.
- No!</i>

01:52.520 --> 01:55.400
- No, I'm not.
- Just get out of the... I got it.

01:55.440 --> 01:58.120
<i>He's trying to tow my car.</i>
He won't even look under the hood.

01:58.160 --> 02:00.800
It might be a simple problem:
might not need a tow, right?

02:00.840 --> 02:03.400
<i>He's gonna charge me
$1,000 if he tows it.</i>

02:03.440 --> 02:05.440
And you won't even look under the hood?

02:05.520 --> 02:07.520
I said I got it.
So why don't you just fuck off?

02:07.600 --> 02:09.520
Maybe the cops can sort this out.

02:09.600 --> 02:12.880
Guy wants his fucking ass kicked.
[ cell phone ringing ]

02:15.760 --> 02:17.680
- Dieter!
- Frank, I've been thinking...

02:17.960 --> 02:20.800
<i>- Can you hold on a minute?
- Oh, Frank, is this a bad time?</i>

02:20.840 --> 02:23.520
- Would you mind?
- Oh...

02:25.560 --> 02:28.960
- Dieter, just stay on the line.
- I'm gonna fuck you up.

02:31.200 --> 02:33.440
Oh!

02:33.480 --> 02:35.360
[ cracking sound ]
Ah!

02:53.600 --> 02:57.160
Dieter, still there?
What's the problem with your car?

02:57.240 --> 03:00.760
Uh, it, it just won't turn over.

03:00.800 --> 03:02.880
There's this clicking
and then it just goes dead.

03:02.920 --> 03:05.160
<i>Did you get that, Dieter?
There's a clicking and it goes dead.</i>

03:05.240 --> 03:09.120
- It's a Hyundai Tiburon, '98.
- Oh yeah, it's a fuse.

03:09.200 --> 03:11.280
Go to the fuses, and
unplug the top right one.

03:13.120 --> 03:16.480
Okay, try it now.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.120
[ the engine turns over ]
You're a genius.

03:29.200 --> 03:31.960
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.600
She should say thank you to me.

03:33.880 --> 03:35.960
<i>- Is she pretty, Frank?</i>
- Gorgeous.

03:36.440 --> 03:39.280
Do you have time for a drink?
Or can I give you my number?

03:39.360 --> 03:41.280
Again, me!
I should get her number.

03:41.360 --> 03:42.920
<i>Me! Me!</i>

03:43.000 --> 03:46.120
Yeah. Funny.

03:46.200 --> 03:49.040
Yes, absolutely.

