05:00.480 --> 05:03.600
[ cell phone ringing ]
Did you take care of the car?

05:03.680 --> 05:06.560
It's running again, yes.
I got to tell you something.

05:06.600 --> 05:09.800
I'd like to see other clients.

05:09.840 --> 05:14.600
- Okay.
- It's not personal, you know.

05:14.680 --> 05:16.840
Do what you need to do
for your business, Dieter.

05:16.880 --> 05:20.480
<i>My business? It's my peace of mind.
You come with trouble.</i>

05:20.520 --> 05:23.560
These cars are like my babies.

05:23.600 --> 05:27.240
Who gets babies lodged in
cement or blown up, you know?

05:27.320 --> 05:32.320
I'd like to meet clients with
maybe not so much Sturm und Drang.

05:32.360 --> 05:37.200
- I respect your decision.
- Thank you.

05:41.160 --> 05:43.000
<i>Hey buddy, got a couple
of bucks? Help a guy out?</i>

05:43.280 --> 05:46.600
- You have something for me?
- Sure. Give me five bucks.

05:46.640 --> 05:51.360
- It was a couple of bucks a second ago.
- Time's money, pal.

05:58.600 --> 06:03.360
- Well?
- What I got for you is advice.

06:05.720 --> 06:07.760
Just because somebody
says have a nice day,

06:07.840 --> 06:10.240
doesn't mean it's gonna happen.

06:16.160 --> 06:19.120
What was that?

06:29.200 --> 06:31.120
<i>Yes, Frank?</i>

06:31.200 --> 06:36.960
- The drop's late.
- A message just came in this second.

06:37.000 --> 06:40.720
Odd timing.
The client's asking where you are.

06:41.000 --> 06:44.400
<i>Where I'm supposed to be.</i>
Tell them to forget about it.

06:44.480 --> 06:47.200
I must have sent you bad coordinates...

06:47.280 --> 06:50.160
That's never happened before.
Why Toronto of all places?

06:50.240 --> 06:53.600
What do we know about Toronto,
Frank? Nothing.

06:53.640 --> 06:56.800
<i>The whole reason you're there
is to open up a new market.</i>

06:56.840 --> 06:59.640
This client is very well connected,
and things are just

06:59.920 --> 07:02.720
too hot in France now.
Even Tarconi says you should lay low.

07:02.800 --> 07:05.680
Tarconi?
When did you speak to Tarconi?

07:05.760 --> 07:09.120
- We talk sometimes.
- About what?

07:09.200 --> 07:12.640
Mostly how to keep you out of trouble.

07:12.720 --> 07:15.200
I can take care of myself, Carla.

07:21.640 --> 07:27.640
- Okay, so where are we going?
- Sending coordinates now.

07:27.680 --> 07:32.240
- <i>Well, send the right ones.</i>
- Have a nice day, Frank.

07:34.680 --> 07:37.720
<i>"Have a nice day."</i>

08:07.280 --> 08:09.720
Be on time, or I'll be gone.

08:22.360 --> 08:24.440
Sorry, buddy.
It kinda got away from me.

08:26.680 --> 08:29.760
- This won't fit in my car.
- Uh, no, I would say not.

08:29.840 --> 08:32.400
Are you dropping this off?

08:32.440 --> 08:34.360
No, I'm picking it up.
[ car door opening ]

08:34.400 --> 08:37.000
I figured I could get it into the truck,
but I was gonna need some help,

08:37.080 --> 08:39.559
and then the guys in the store
were all, like, go fuck yourself.

08:39.640 --> 08:41.720
<i>[ kids ]: Swear jar! Swear jar!</i>

08:41.799 --> 08:46.680
Felix, Silver, back in the car.
Great. There's another 5 bucks.

08:46.760 --> 08:50.040
Hey, you think you could give me a hand?

08:50.120 --> 08:52.120
Big guy like you, it
shouldn't be too hard.

08:52.160 --> 08:54.800
Sure.

09:03.480 --> 09:04.400
Just slide 'er in the back.

09:04.680 --> 09:06.080
<i>- [ kid ]: It's a TV.
- [ kid ]: No, it's a dryer.</i>

09:06.160 --> 09:09.160
<i>[ kid ]: No, it's a TV.</i>

09:10.480 --> 09:14.560
<i>- Hey, my dad's a jerk.</i>
- Okay, well...

09:16.880 --> 09:20.040
Thanks.
Hey, I got something for you.

09:20.120 --> 09:22.320
No, no, no, I don't mean like that.

09:22.360 --> 09:24.960
Nah, come on. How often do you find
a guy who'll help you out like that?

09:25.040 --> 09:29.640
- No.
- Look, no, take it. You have no idea

09:29.720 --> 09:32.280
how much this means to me.

09:32.360 --> 09:34.600
I'm not going to
take your money, okay?

09:34.680 --> 09:36.120
- Okay.
- Thanks.

09:39.400 --> 09:42.000
- Okay, okay.
- Good luck.

09:42.280 --> 09:43.120
<i>Take care.</i>

10:02.880 --> 10:05.040
<i>- Hey.
- What?</i>

10:05.080 --> 10:08.040
<i>When you see a guy flash
his headlights 3 times,</i>

10:08.080 --> 10:11.320
<i>that's your contact. You're
supposed to follow him.</i>

10:23.520 --> 10:26.920
[ call signal ]
Frank, did you get the information?

10:26.960 --> 10:29.520
<i>I don't know, Carla.
Maybe, maybe not.</i>

10:29.560 --> 10:32.920
<i>I helped a guy with a dryer,
but I still don't have a package.</i>

10:33.000 --> 10:35.400
There's some problem
with getting the package,

10:35.440 --> 10:37.720
but it's supposed to
be cleared up by now.

10:37.800 --> 10:40.720
And now there's something about
some other guy and flashing headlights.

10:40.760 --> 10:44.800
That's the signal for the drop.
It was just delivered to me.

10:44.880 --> 10:50.080
- Could someone be watching you, Frank?
- There's no one here, Carla.

10:50.160 --> 10:52.640
<i>This guy's a major player
in Toronto construction.</i>

10:52.720 --> 10:56.520
<i>He needs this package and
he's getting very nervous.</i>

10:56.560 --> 10:58.320
You're not the one stuck out here in the

10:58.640 --> 11:00.400
middle of nowhere waiting
to get the job done!

11:00.440 --> 11:03.640
<i>You're at home, in Nice,
probably on your porch in your bikini!</i>

11:03.720 --> 11:07.920
How can you say that, Frank?
I'm working just as hard as you!

11:08.440 --> 11:11.280
I know you're upset, but
the deal hasn't changed.

11:11.320 --> 11:13.680
You'll get the pick-up
at the first coordinate.

11:16.040 --> 11:18.000
No one's flashing me, Carla.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.960
<i>Frank? You still there?</i>

11:22.480 --> 11:23.880
Frank?

11:24.600 --> 11:27.120
This is the last job
we're doing for this client.

11:29.000 --> 11:31.920
You sure you're not
getting this through Kagan?

11:32.000 --> 11:35.720
- <i>No, I fired him, remember?</i>
- OK, just checking.

12:12.560 --> 12:15.000
We're all following this guy?

12:59.400 --> 13:02.040
[ grunting ]

13:02.120 --> 13:04.120
Buddy, you okay?
I'm going to help you.

13:04.200 --> 13:06.040
<i>Get me out of here, man!
Get me out of here!</i>

13:06.480 --> 13:09.160
<i>Come on, help! Help me!</i>

13:14.160 --> 13:16.480
<i>Hey, you okay?</i>

13:16.520 --> 13:19.600
Take it easy. Stay calm.
I'm not going to hurt you.

13:22.640 --> 13:24.600
<i>Take it easy.</i>

13:26.160 --> 13:28.480
[ tires screeching ]
Take it easy.

13:28.520 --> 13:31.560
- Oh, fuck no!
- You okay?

13:31.600 --> 13:33.440
<i>Hey!</i>

13:33.480 --> 13:35.560
<i>Drop the knife and kick it away.</i>

13:35.600 --> 13:38.640
<i>On your knees!</i>

13:38.720 --> 13:41.640
- What the hell is this?
- Get on your knees. Hands on your head.

13:50.400 --> 13:52.840
- Let's go.
- Any particular destination?

13:52.880 --> 13:55.720
- Shut the fuck up.
- Will that be a long drive?

13:55.760 --> 13:59.520
- Don't make me tell you twice.
- Could we go easy on the cuffs?

13:59.560 --> 14:03.880
- You want them tighter?
- Mind if I ask who you are?

14:03.960 --> 14:06.600
By the inimitable sense of
style and welcoming demeanour,

14:06.680 --> 14:11.440
- I assume you're cops.
- You must be looking for a kick in the nuts.

14:11.520 --> 14:15.400
I was right. You are cops.
So where are we going?

14:15.440 --> 14:18.560
Where do detectives
usually take suspects, huh?

14:18.600 --> 14:24.720
Lunch? Massage parlour?
Back to your place?

14:48.000 --> 14:50.400
I don't want to ask any questions
that are too complicated,

14:50.440 --> 14:52.920
- but what are we doing here?
- You're being charged.

14:52.960 --> 14:54.840
What the fuck do you think?

14:54.880 --> 14:57.760
- Mind if I ask what for?
- Murder.

15:04.480 --> 15:07.600
[ door signal ]

15:09.920 --> 15:13.200
I'm Detective Ryder.
My partner, Detective Stanwick.

15:13.280 --> 15:18.520
So, Mr., uh...
Martin Francis.

15:18.560 --> 15:20.960
You want to give us your
version of the story?

15:22.000 --> 15:27.440
- There were 3 little pigs...
- The story with this car, jackass.

15:27.520 --> 15:31.120
- I wasn't driving that car.
- Stanwick, you see anyone else driving that car?

15:32.680 --> 15:36.080
Recognize him?

15:37.600 --> 15:40.880
Guy asked for a hand out,
gave him a couple of bucks.

15:40.960 --> 15:42.080
Not all you gave him, I'd say.

15:42.400 --> 15:44.120
I have no idea what he's
doing in the trunk of that car.

15:44.160 --> 15:46.720
- You were driving that car, numbnuts.
- Enough with the insults.

15:46.760 --> 15:48.640
I. Was. Not. Driving.
That. Car.

15:48.720 --> 15:52.440
What car were you driving?

15:52.480 --> 15:55.600
My name is Martin Francis,
I live in France, I'm here

15:55.920 --> 15:59.040
enjoying a wonderful holiday,
I'm driving a rental,

15:59.080 --> 16:01.280
I see a kid driving that car...

16:01.320 --> 16:05.440
<i>looked like he was in trouble.</i>
So I tried to help him out.

16:05.520 --> 16:10.640
There are no records
of any rental cars in your name.

16:10.720 --> 16:13.400
There was only one car at the
terminal, and you got out of it,

16:13.440 --> 16:16.240
and you're saying you know nothing
about this body, you didn't move it,

16:16.320 --> 16:19.400
- had nothing to do with it?
- By George, I think he's got it.

16:22.200 --> 16:24.240
These're your prints.

16:26.120 --> 16:29.800
The prints on the bill are also yours.

16:35.440 --> 16:42.520
Yeah, that's the guy.
He gave me 50 bucks to move the box.

16:42.560 --> 16:44.640
If I had known what was in it, I
never would have given him a hand.

16:44.720 --> 16:46.440
Get him out of here.

16:50.840 --> 16:53.400
Look, I don't know what's
going on, but obviously...

16:53.680 --> 16:56.520
Shut the fuck up. You're being
held pending arraignment on Monday.

16:59.800 --> 17:02.680
Do I get a phone call?

17:02.720 --> 17:05.319
[ call signal ]
Yes, Frank?

17:05.400 --> 17:09.000
Call Tarconi. Tell him I'm being held
in Toronto on some trumped-up charge.

17:09.079 --> 17:11.240
<i>What?
What did you do this time?</i>

17:11.319 --> 17:14.440
I haven't done anything, Carla,
but somebody wants me in jail.

17:17.280 --> 17:19.599
Gotcha.

17:23.640 --> 17:27.400
[ cell phone ringing ]

17:27.480 --> 17:29.960
<i>- Allô?
- Inspector Tarconi?</i>

17:30.040 --> 17:32.600
It's Carla. Frank has been arrested
in Toronto. He needs your help.

17:32.680 --> 17:35.440
I have an associate
with Toronto law enforcement.

17:35.480 --> 17:41.080
- Tell me where he's being held.
- The Gerrard Street jail.

17:41.560 --> 17:43.040
<i>What?</i>

17:43.120 --> 17:45.840
We must get him out of
there as soon as possible.

18:00.120 --> 18:01.840
Witness the seal.

18:05.120 --> 18:06.880
Sign across the tape.

18:27.160 --> 18:29.480
<i>Have a nice day.</i>

18:33.960 --> 18:36.600
[ whistling ]

18:36.680 --> 18:38.520
[ grunting ]

18:38.600 --> 18:41.520
[ whooping and whistling ]

18:43.360 --> 18:45.880
Hold up.

19:04.720 --> 19:06.520
You want to tell me
what this is all about?

19:06.600 --> 19:09.520
I don't know what you mean, man.
I'm just, I'm here on a drugs charge.

19:09.600 --> 19:12.080
I'm just waiting to see my lawyer.

19:12.120 --> 19:14.600
Hey, Peaches.
See you in the shower.

19:17.840 --> 19:21.680
- Those two giving you a hard time?
- Yeah.

19:23.400 --> 19:27.200
Want me to call them back?

19:28.240 --> 19:29.960
So talk.

19:33.080 --> 19:36.000
They said they were
going to reduce my charge.

19:36.880 --> 19:40.840
- All I was supposed to do was drive the car...
- What about the body in the trunk?

19:41.120 --> 19:42.240
I didn't know anything about that.

19:42.320 --> 19:45.480
And now I'm being charged
with conspiracy and escape.

19:45.520 --> 19:47.880
They're trying to fuck me!

19:47.920 --> 19:50.960
Who told you to do this?
The cop? Ryder?

19:55.040 --> 19:59.760
So, gorgeous, what are you in for?
Modeling without a license?

19:59.840 --> 20:03.440
Speeding.
Parking tickets. The usual.

20:03.520 --> 20:06.800
Oh, I get it, you two
are a couple. That's nice.

20:06.880 --> 20:08.760
It's gonna be a long
weekend for this one.

20:08.840 --> 20:12.400
- Why don't you two move along?
- Ask us nicely.

20:16.360 --> 20:18.760
[ men shouting ]

20:53.440 --> 20:56.680
[ men booing ]

21:00.320 --> 21:02.800
What did they tell you?

21:02.880 --> 21:06.160
<i>Sorry, man,
I got the kids to think about.</i>

21:06.640 --> 21:10.280
<i>Party's over.
Back to your cells. Now!</i>

21:36.320 --> 21:39.880
<i>Frank has been charged with murder.</i>

21:39.960 --> 21:42.000
I'm not sure what my people can do.

21:42.080 --> 21:45.480
Where was Frank going,
and who was the job for?

21:45.520 --> 21:48.000
I'll talk to the Canadian client
and get all the information I can.

21:48.040 --> 21:50.960
They must do it quickly,
because once Frank's in the system,

21:51.040 --> 21:53.280
there is not much they
can do to help him.

21:53.320 --> 21:57.080
- There will be a long trial.
- And with all the shit

21:57.160 --> 22:00.360
Frank's been involved with,
he'll go away for a long time.

22:20.080 --> 22:23.400
What the hell?

22:29.960 --> 22:32.480
Finally an address.

22:32.520 --> 22:36.440
171 Liberty.

22:36.520 --> 22:41.160
8675309.
And where's the package?

22:51.920 --> 22:56.600
Ja, I could install a cold air intake,
a higher torque converter.

22:56.640 --> 22:58.400
- Maybe swap out the rev limiter chip...
- How much?

22:58.480 --> 23:01.440
Don't you want to know
what I'm going to do with it?

23:01.480 --> 23:05.760
Just make it fast as hell.
And a sound system to blow my balls off.

23:05.800 --> 23:07.360
You know what I can do
with the sound system...

23:07.640 --> 23:09.560
I don't care. Just do it.
Look, here's an advance.

23:09.600 --> 23:14.280
It's gotta look good, drive fast
and sound like I'm at a rock show.

23:14.360 --> 23:18.400
- Now, what about rims?
- Rims...

23:18.480 --> 23:24.960
- make a car look like a whore.
- Exactly. So, you'll do it?

23:26.880 --> 23:30.080
- Sure. Yeah.
- This'll be great.

23:31.360 --> 23:33.920
It's gonna be great.

23:42.520 --> 23:43.680
Let's go.

23:43.720 --> 23:47.280
- You call this room service?
- Fuck you, smartass.

23:47.360 --> 23:49.640
You wanna spend another night here?

23:49.720 --> 23:52.800
Like you've got some say
in where I spend the night.

23:53.800 --> 23:56.320
I figured they'd want me in one piece.

24:02.080 --> 24:05.160
[ whistling ]

24:10.800 --> 24:12.840
Good luck, man.

24:19.680 --> 24:23.160
[ door opening ]

24:25.120 --> 24:28.120
Thanks for picking up my dry cleaning.

24:32.160 --> 24:35.040
Try that again, you
prick, you better mean it.

24:35.080 --> 24:37.920
I'm going to find out
what you're up to, Ryder.

24:42.880 --> 24:45.120
Go ahead.

24:48.800 --> 24:51.640
<i>There seems to have been some mistake.</i>

24:51.680 --> 24:55.600
- Oh, really?
- Detective Stanwick jumped to conclusions

24:55.680 --> 25:00.920
a little rapidly. And although we
appreciate his efforts, some, uh,

25:00.960 --> 25:02.960
incorrect assumptions were made.

25:03.040 --> 25:06.360
Cut to the chase, boys.
You're going to release me, why not just do it?

25:06.400 --> 25:10.160
- There are some... formalities.
- Sit down.

25:16.440 --> 25:19.160
You have the sincere apologies
of both myself and my colleagues.

25:19.240 --> 25:22.280
You don't want me to press charges.

25:22.360 --> 25:25.160
That would be the most
favourable outcome, yes.

25:25.240 --> 25:29.040
Detective Stanwick has two children
who are about to begin college.

25:29.080 --> 25:31.640
The fact is, the loss of
his income would mean that

25:31.960 --> 25:34.520
they would lose their
chance at a good education

25:34.560 --> 25:39.120
and, you know,
become a burden on society.

25:39.160 --> 25:41.840
Maybe they could work for you,
Detective Ryder.

25:41.880 --> 25:45.080
That way they'd still have
a job and be a burden on society.

25:45.160 --> 25:51.440
Ahem. My, uh,
suggestion would be

25:51.480 --> 25:53.520
that you take the opportunity
to walk the fuck out of here

25:53.560 --> 25:55.960
before Detective
Stanwick changes his mind

25:56.040 --> 25:59.080
and you leave here in a bag.

26:02.400 --> 26:05.440
A little privacy, gentlemen?

26:35.120 --> 26:37.040
Martin Francis.

26:37.080 --> 26:40.920
- Sign here. And sign here.
- Yep.

26:40.960 --> 26:45.360
Personal property stays sealed
until you've left the facility.

27:10.400 --> 27:13.240
Hey, Steve McQueen!
No hard feelings, eh?

27:13.320 --> 27:19.440
No feelings at all, Detective.
No feelings at all.

27:28.680 --> 27:31.760
[ call signal ]
Oh, that's him. Frank!

27:31.800 --> 27:33.840
<i>You've got to get out of Canada.
You're not safe.</i>

27:33.920 --> 27:36.520
<i>Why, Carla, I'm just
starting to enjoy myself.</i>

27:36.560 --> 27:38.680
- Frank, it's Tarconi.
- Hello, Inspector.

27:38.800 --> 27:42.800
- How's the weather at my house?
<i>- Oh please, this is no time for jokes.</i>

27:42.840 --> 27:46.840
Frank, some very dangerous men
are fighting over land in Toronto.

27:46.920 --> 27:49.080
Another dead man means nothing to them.

27:49.160 --> 27:51.800
I just spent the night in jail.
I intend to find out why.

27:51.880 --> 27:55.320
Get rid of the package you are
carrying, and get out of there.

27:55.400 --> 27:58.080
- You have one chance.
- Do what he says, okay?

27:58.160 --> 28:00.120
I'm afraid that won't be possible.

28:00.440 --> 28:03.400
And for a change, I'm
going to deliberately

28:03.680 --> 28:05.400
- break one of the rules.
<i>- No!</i>

28:05.520 --> 28:09.080
Yes, Carla.
I'm going to open the package.

28:14.280 --> 28:17.640
<i>- So, what have we got?</i>
- Here we are.

28:17.680 --> 28:23.040
520 horsepower at 6300 rpm.
That means from 0 to 100

28:23.120 --> 28:26.400
in 3 seconds, maybe 3.1.
Then I've installed 16 speakers

28:26.480 --> 28:29.200
in Harman Kardon...
it's just over 300 kph.

28:29.240 --> 28:31.360
Whatever.

28:32.160 --> 28:37.520
Oh, ho, ho, ho, ho, look at those rims.
Now that's what makes a car.

28:37.600 --> 28:40.880
Okay, the fuel consumption
is just actually better...

28:40.960 --> 28:44.320
Dude, I don't care. Whatever you did,

28:44.400 --> 28:47.440
- I'm sure it's fine.
- It's not really a 'whatever.' Are you kidding?

28:47.480 --> 28:49.200
I don't care about the details.

28:49.240 --> 28:53.040
Can I pull chicks with it?
Is it going to look good down on the Croisette?

28:53.080 --> 28:54.840
Will people be jealous?

28:54.920 --> 28:58.200
- Yes, to all those things.
- Then I don't care about the rest.

28:59.240 --> 29:01.760
- Get out.
- What?

29:01.840 --> 29:04.800
I don't want to see you again.
You have no respect for the car. For the process.

29:04.880 --> 29:08.360
- You're just a fucking asshole.
- Yeah. OK. But I've got money.

29:08.440 --> 29:10.400
So you're a rich asshole.

29:12.240 --> 29:14.280
I thought you said it was fast.

29:15.840 --> 29:20.320
Hey! Oh, come on now.
Just take it off the fucking lift, man.

29:53.120 --> 29:55.360
[ call signal ]
Frank...

29:55.400 --> 29:58.360
- Did you open the package?
- Yep.

29:58.440 --> 30:01.000
- What is it?
- It's a human hand, Carla.

30:01.040 --> 30:03.040
A severed human hand.

30:03.080 --> 30:04.960
<i>Get out of there, Frank.
We'll cancel the contract.</i>

30:05.000 --> 30:07.280
<i>- Just go!</i>
- I've been attacked, insulted

30:07.360 --> 30:10.280
and thrown in jail just to
get me the package. The client

30:10.320 --> 30:13.240
<i>obviously went to a lot of trouble.
We owe them a delivery.</i>

30:13.320 --> 30:15.640
We've built a business
on customer satisfaction.

30:15.720 --> 30:18.840
I'm not changing our policy now.
You can inform the client I'm

30:18.880 --> 30:20.800
- on my way to the drop.
<i>- Okay, Frank.</i>

30:20.840 --> 30:24.360
You're looking for a slim
blonde woman at the drop.

30:24.440 --> 30:28.160
<i>She'll be wearing
a silver snakeskin dress.</i>

30:37.000 --> 30:41.000
Oh, for crying out loud.
Not this bullshit again.

31:11.320 --> 31:13.400
<i>Give me the hand.</i>

31:37.680 --> 31:39.880
That's got to hurt.

31:56.120 --> 31:58.880
Hi, I'm Jenny. Welcome.
Membership number?

32:01.360 --> 32:07.000
- 8675309.
- Nice to see you, Mr... Nonumes?

32:07.040 --> 32:11.520
- It's No Names.
- Of course. No names. First visit?

32:11.600 --> 32:13.800
- Mm-hmm.
- The lockers are right down there.

32:14.080 --> 32:17.120
I have to ask.
The numbers on your fingernails?

32:17.200 --> 32:18.720
My phone number.

32:18.800 --> 32:21.560
Cute, right?
A number for each finger.

32:21.600 --> 32:24.760
And even one for the thumbs.

32:29.280 --> 32:32.200
[ dance music ]

32:47.840 --> 32:50.400
If you have something
for me, give it to me now.

32:50.680 --> 32:53.440
- It's not for you.
- How do you know it's not?

33:00.240 --> 33:02.200
Give me a hand.

33:17.680 --> 33:20.040
Well, look who's back.

33:21.760 --> 33:25.160
The man pulling the strings.
But who's the passenger?

33:25.240 --> 33:27.480
- Everyone out, gym's closing.

33:27.520 --> 33:31.160
- The package.
- You should stick to being a bodybuilder.

33:33.040 --> 33:37.160
You can either give it to me,
or I can just take it.

33:37.440 --> 33:39.640
Boys, I need a hand.

35:23.000 --> 35:25.080
Enough!

35:41.240 --> 35:44.720
I believe this is for you.

36:02.280 --> 36:05.200
Oh, my God.

36:20.440 --> 36:23.360
I'm sorry if you had any
problems with my security.

36:23.440 --> 36:25.120
There was no difficulty.

36:29.240 --> 36:31.160
Do you see the tattoo on this hand?

36:31.440 --> 36:35.199
My uncle and my father
were part of a business group.

36:35.200 --> 36:39.920
They own 25% of downtown.
Now I run the company.

36:44.240 --> 36:46.560
They wanted to develop the
city but keep its character,

36:46.840 --> 36:49.120
its history. They were dreamers,
but this was their vision.

36:49.400 --> 36:52.600
It started with Phillips Square.
Now it has a life of its own.

36:52.680 --> 36:54.920
The city is feeding on itself.

36:56.760 --> 36:59.200
A guy named Adam Smith
set up my uncle.

37:04.360 --> 37:07.680
My uncle took the fall for killing a guy.

37:07.760 --> 37:11.600
Then Smith had my uncle killed in jail.

37:11.960 --> 37:13.680
Because my father
refused to sell him one

37:14.000 --> 37:15.720
final building that
he wanted to tear down.

37:16.240 --> 37:20.400
- That's your uncle's hand.
- Yes.

37:22.320 --> 37:26.560
The problem Smith had
was getting proof of my

37:26.840 --> 37:31.280
uncle's death to my father.
That's why they hired you.

37:31.320 --> 37:34.720
The prison authorities were trying to
keep the hand from getting out of the jail.

37:36.120 --> 37:40.720
<i>Personal property stays sealed
until you've left the facility.</i>

37:40.800 --> 37:41.120
They search everyone as they
leave, but they can't search

37:41.400 --> 37:44.280
- a prisoner's belongings.
- Especially a sealed envelope.

37:44.360 --> 37:47.080
I noticed you opened
the package already.

37:47.120 --> 37:49.640
Someone went to an awful
lot of trouble to get me

37:49.920 --> 37:54.000
- that package. I had to know.
- I would have opened it, too.

37:55.680 --> 37:57.640
My uncle's death will start a land war.

37:57.680 --> 38:01.560
For every building that goes up,
30 bodies will go down.

38:01.640 --> 38:03.760
It's the final phase
of Smith's land grab.

38:03.840 --> 38:07.080
So my night in jail, that was
all set up just to get the hand out.

38:07.160 --> 38:09.080
Detective Ryder.

38:11.040 --> 38:13.360
He promises inmates
help with their parole,

38:13.440 --> 38:16.680
gets them to help with his little games.

38:16.760 --> 38:18.920
This war will begin with
the death of my father.

38:18.960 --> 38:22.560
Let's see if we can do something
about that before things get out of hand.

38:22.600 --> 38:25.480
Ah, the lovebirds from cell block 6.

38:27.560 --> 38:30.920
- Ryder.
- You're done.

38:30.960 --> 38:33.000
I'm not one of your jailbirds, Ryder.

38:33.080 --> 38:38.480
<i>Adam Smith.
You've got some brass balls coming here.</i>

38:38.760 --> 38:41.080
I'm not afraid of you.

38:41.880 --> 38:46.560
End of the line, Transporter.
We'll finish this delivery.

38:46.600 --> 38:51.560
You hired me.
And now you're changing the deal.

39:00.400 --> 39:03.960
Turn around.
Put your hands on your head.

39:13.280 --> 39:16.480
You guys get out on good behaviour?

39:37.560 --> 39:40.320
I got this.

40:10.480 --> 40:12.640
<i>Sign the papers.</i>

40:14.320 --> 40:17.160
Look, your brother's dead,
your power base is gone.

40:17.440 --> 40:20.880
Your lieutenants, they're already
fighting for a piece of this.

40:20.960 --> 40:23.720
Toronto.
Rhymes with money.

40:28.960 --> 40:31.840
- <i>Carla.</i>
- It's about time, Frank.

40:31.880 --> 40:33.800
Precisely what I don't have.

40:33.880 --> 40:36.640
Call Tarconi, have him
find a Detective Stanwick.

40:36.680 --> 40:40.080
- He's the one who set you up?
- No, it's the other guy, Ryder.

40:40.360 --> 40:41.920
GPS me, give Tarconi the information.

40:42.000 --> 40:45.280
<i>Tell him that Ryder is
dirty and I have proof.</i>

40:46.880 --> 40:52.200
You were at my daughter's
christening. And now all of this?

40:52.280 --> 40:56.840
It's not personal.
He just wants that building.

40:56.920 --> 40:59.680
- He won't kill me, Dad.
- He killed your uncle.

40:59.760 --> 41:01.800
No, no, if you sign this contract,

41:01.880 --> 41:04.320
then everything you've
ever worked for is gone.

41:04.400 --> 41:08.160
If I don't, then everything
I have ever lived for is gone.

41:15.480 --> 41:17.520
And now you're both dead.
[ gasping ]

41:20.360 --> 41:22.560
Ah!!!

41:26.640 --> 41:29.440
Dad, call the police!

41:30.640 --> 41:34.640
<i>Police! The Adam Smith
construction project downtown.</i>

41:58.000 --> 42:00.920
Thought you might need a hand.

42:09.120 --> 42:11.360
<i>You know, all you had
to do was say thank you,</i>

42:11.440 --> 42:12.600
and I would have stood by you.

42:12.880 --> 42:16.120
But no, I was supposed
to take the fall for everything.

42:16.200 --> 42:17.880
What the fuck does that mean?

42:18.160 --> 42:22.560
- A little appreciation goes a long way.
- Shut the fuck up, Stanwick.

42:28.280 --> 42:32.240
You should hang on to that building.
It's good to keep a little of the past alive.

42:32.280 --> 42:37.000
- It will never be torn down.
<i>- I owe you a debt of gratitude.</i>

42:37.080 --> 42:39.680
This city will never be able to
thank you for what you've done.

42:39.760 --> 42:43.200
But I must ask...
my brother's hand?

42:43.280 --> 42:45.960
Lost in the shuffle.
Best forgotten.

42:48.040 --> 42:53.040
Frank...
will I see you again?

42:53.080 --> 42:56.600
The next time I'm in Toronto,
I'll swing by.

42:57.960 --> 43:00.400
I'd like that.

43:07.320 --> 43:10.280
[ dog barking ]

43:32.200 --> 43:34.680
[ cell phone ringing ]

43:36.720 --> 43:38.560
<i>Hey, Frank.</i>

43:38.640 --> 43:41.120
When are you coming back?
I got the red car

43:41.200 --> 43:44.680
ready for you to drive again.
No mishaps this time.

43:44.760 --> 43:49.360
- How did it go seeing other clients?
<i>- Oh, it was great. Fine.</i>

43:49.440 --> 43:52.720
It was bad.
He didn't appreciate me.

43:52.760 --> 43:54.520
I appreciate you, Dieter.

43:54.560 --> 43:57.840
See? A little appreciation
goes a long way.

43:57.880 --> 44:00.600
I know, Dieter, I know.

